Figure 1 – Wave Functions:
Displays the normalized wave functions of a particle confined in a one-dimensional infinite potential well for the first four quantum states.
As the quantum number increases, the wavefunction exhibits more nodes, 
reflecting the higher-energy standing-wave solutions of the Schrödinger equation.

Figure 2 – Probability Density:
Illustrates the probability density distributions corresponding to each quantum state. 
The plots show the probability of finding the particle at different positions within the box. 
The increasing number of peaks with higher quantum numbers demonstrates the quantized nature of the particle's spatial distribution.
